text: “Protest and free speech are a part of Oakland’s DNA, but I am asking people to stay home," said Oakland mayor Libby Schaaf, after Friday night's demonstration devolved into a vandalism and looting spree. https://t.co/qsYSU4mByo

name: sfchronicle
text: Live Updates: Protesters and police began gathering near Frank H. Ogawa Plaza in Oakland just before 6 p.m. — about 20 people and four Oakland police SUVs.  https://t.co/66vu87AW4p

name: sfchronicle
text:
A woman was arrested and booked for attempted murder after a vehicle drove into protesters in San Jose yesterday, police said. The vehicle ran over two men, then drove toward a crowd of protesters and Santa Clara County deputies.

Read more live updates: https://t.co/YKy1P93oGt

name: sfchronicle
text:
A small group of S.F. protesters stood face-to-face with police at 17th Street and Mission Avenue, yelling and taunting, but otherwise remaining peaceful. 

"Say his name! George Floyd," they yelled.

For updates: https://t.co/CDLTM09f5L

name: sfchronicle
text:

name: sfchronicle
text:
In Oakland, people are marching from 14th Street and Broadway to Lake Merritt to protest the police killing of George Floyd in Minneapolis.

For updates: https://t.co/yo4wAY4SI0 https://t.co/lvpg5JYMM9

text: RT @mgafni: And march is back to 14th and Broadway where a line of officers blocks southbound to police station https://t.co/a3jjflXq2F
